post_text:
The US Department of Agriculture has approved a waiver allowing schools to serve free reimbursable meals to ALL students through December 31st. The dates of the waiver are from September 1st through December 31st and is available to both in person or remote learners. As a result, all in person students will have the option to receive a free lunch and/or breakfast each day beginning on Tuesday, September 8th. Any lunch bills sent out for this school year will only reflect charges through August 31st. For remote learners, meals will be distributed on Monday and Thursdays only from 1:30-3:00 in the back parking lot by the gym at Flora Elementary School beginning on Thursday, September 10th. On Mondays, remote learning students will be provided meals for Monday through Wednesday and on Thursday they will be provided meals for Thursday and Friday.
We greatly appreciate the waiver provided by USDA and are excited to be able to offer this opportunity to our students!!
If you have any questions, please contact the unit office at 618-662-2412 or email jhackney@floraschools.com

post_text:
On Wednesday, August 12th IDPH and ISBE released guidance that indicated neck gaiters would not be allowed as a face covering. We submitted a couple of possible modifications to see if that would lead to the gaiters being allowed. We received word today that even with the modifications we submitted, neck gaiters do not meet the requirements for face coverings.

If your child has issues wearing the ear loop masks recommended, please contact the nurses’ office and they can offer some alternatives that might work for your student. We apologize for the inconvenience and appreciate your patience and understanding as we continue to work through the guidelines.

post_text:
A few reminders:
Online registration for the 2020-2021 school year ends today. If you haven't registered your child for school please go to www.floraschools.com and fill out the registration forms. If your child will be riding the bus to or from school, you can call the bus barn any time after August 10th to get pick up and drop off times and locations. Chromebook pick up for 7th-8th grade students will be August 6, 4:30-6:30 P.M. This will be at the Flora Jr. High in the front of the building.
Please drive through the circle drive where we will have people to assist you with this process.

One change to the return to school/remote learning plan is that any student that is enrolled in the district-either in person or remote learning-will be eligible to participate in extracurricular activities.

post_text:
Floyd Henson Jr. High 7th and 8th grade chromebook Pick up

All Flora Jr. High students will receive a chromebook this year to use at school.
We are having a pick up date for 7th and 8th grade students on Thursday,
August 6, 4:30-6:30 P.M. This will be at the Flora Jr. High in the front of the building.
Please drive through the circle drive where we will have people to assist you with this process.
We will need you to sign a form and pay for the insurance on the device. The insurance is $25.00 per device. If insurance isn’t purchased and something happens to the device, you’ll owe $250.00 to purchase a new one. 6th grade students will pick up their device during 6th grade orientation that will take place on August 11. (more details to come on this) If you have any questions, you can contact the school at 618-662-8394.

post_text:
Flora Elementary will be distributing grade cards and school supplies for grades Pre-K through 5th on Monday, May 18 from 1:00-7:00. During this time, any additional packets, Chromebooks, bus tags, library books, band instruments, and textbooks will be collected. Items can be turned in at the Flora Elementary School by the covered patio area in the southeast parking lot behind the school. Tables will be set up by grade levels beginning with Pre-K. If you have multiple students, you will need to stop at each grade level table, and staff members will collect items from you. There will be a designated table for fees and lunch bill collection.

More information regarding Pre-school screening will be provided at a later date.

Yearbooks will be issued in the fall.

We appreciate your cooperation during these challenging times.

post_text:
FHS CHEER TRYOUT 2020

When: Friday , May 1st at 4 pm

How: submit tryout video to keade@floraschools.com

Video requirements: verbal statement of which squad you are trying out for (football, basketball, both) , toe touch, double jump of your choice, individual floor cheer, individual sideline cheer, and a verbal statement of the level of tumbling you can do. (No tumbling should be performed unless on a mat)

Essay submission: 3 paragraphs about why you want to be a FHS cheerleader and how you can benefit FHS cheerleading

What to wear: orange and blue shirt with shorts, hair pulled up with bow, and tennis shoes .

Results will be posted by 9pm Friday May 1st on the cheer BAND APP and SCHOOL DISTRICT Facebook page

VIDEOS MUST BE SUBMITTED VIA EMAIL

NO LATE SUBMISSIONS ACCEPTED

post_text:
24/7 Statewide Hotline: COVID-19

The Illinois Department of Public Health (IDPH) in coordination with the Illinois Poison Control Center have launched the Illinois Novel Coronavirus (COVID-19) Hotline and email address to answer questions Local Health Departments, clinicians, and the general public may have regarding the 2019 novel Coronavirus.

The hotline and email address were created to provide consistent information, answer questions, share facts about symptoms, and provide up-to-date information from the CDC.

Illinoisans can dial 1-800-889-3931 twenty-four hours a day, seven days a week or email DPH.SICK@ILLINOIS.GOV to get their questions answered.

There will be NO students involved in this training exercise.

birth to three are being offered by Flora Unit #35 P.A.T.

March 23rd to March 26th
, 2020. Parents/guardians are
encouraged to have children screened during the critical ages

of developmental delays will benefit a child for a lifetime. If
you are interested, please call 662-6502 or 662-2014 for an
appointment.

FHS would like to invite our 8th grade and their parents to our 8th Grade/Freshmen "Registration Info Night." It will be on Wednesday, February 12 at 7:00 PM in the FHS Harry Penry Auditorium. Students will turn in their registration form requesting freshmen classes on this date.

It would be very beneficial for your child and at least one parent to attend. We will have staff members in attendance to give an overview of each department's class offerings. We will talk about scheduling Freshman level classes and four-year planning as well. Staff members will be there to assist, advise or answer any questions. It will last approximately 45 minutes and then you can feel free to explore our building and ask questions. We will stick around and ask individual questions as long as it takes.

Contact us if you have any questions. Our office hours are 7:30 to 4:00 PM and our number is 618.662.8316
